{"title_page": "Poederoijen", "text_new": "{{Infobox settlement\n| name                    = Poederoijen\n| settlement_type         = Village\n| other_name              = <!-- if different from name -->\n| native_name             = <!-- if different from name -->\n| native_name_lang        = nl\n| image_skyline           =\n| image_alt               =\n| image_caption           =\n| image_flag              =\n| image_shield            = Poederoijen wapen.svg\n| nickname                =\n| motto                   =\n| image_map               = LocatieZaltbommel.png\n| map_caption             =\n| image_map1              = Map NL - Zaltbommel - Poederoijen.png\n| map_caption1            = The village centre (red) and the statistical district (light green) of Poederoijen in the municipality of Zaltbommel.\n| pushpin_map             = <!-- Netherlands -->\n| pushpin_label_position  =\n| pushpin_map_caption     = Location in the Netherlands\n| subdivision_type        = [[List of sovereign states|Country]]\n| subdivision_name        = [[Netherlands]]\n| subdivision_type1       = [[Provinces of the Netherlands|Province]]\n| subdivision_name1       = [[Gelderland]]\n| subdivision_type2       = [[List of municipalities of the Netherlands|Municipality]]\n| subdivision_name2       = [[Zaltbommel]]\n| leader_title            =\n| leader_name             =\n| leader_party            =\n| coordinates             = {{coord|51|47|8|N|5|4|49|E|region:NL_type:city(986)|display=inline,title}}\n| coordinates_footnotes   =\n| elevation_m             =\n| elevation_min_m         =\n| elevation_max_m         =\n| area_footnotes          =\n| area_total_km2          =\n| established_title       =\n| established_date        =\n| population_footnotes    = <!-- for references: use <ref> tags -->\n| population_total        = 986\n| population_as_of        = 1 January 2010\n| population_demonym      =\n| population_note         =\n| population_density_km2  = auto\n| timezone                = [[Central European Time|CET]]\n| utc_offset              = +1\n| timezone_DST            = [[Central European Summer Time|CEST]]\n| utc_offset_DST          = +2\n| postal_code_type        = [[List of postal codes in the Netherlands|Postal code]]\n| postal_code             = 5307\n| area_code_type          = [[Telephone numbers in the Netherlands|Dialing code]]\n| area_code               =\n| website                 =\n| footnotes               =\n}}\n'''Poederoijen''' is a village in the [[Netherlands|Dutch]] province of [[Gelderland]]. It is a part of the municipality of [[Zaltbommel]], and lies about 9&nbsp;km southeast of [[Gorinchem]].\n\nPoederoijen was a separate municipality until 1955, when it was merged with [[Brakel, Gelderland|Brakel]].<ref>{{Repertorium Nederlandse Gemeenten}}</ref>\n\nIn 2001, the village of Poederoijen had 398 inhabitants. The built-up area of the village was 0.083&nbsp;km\u00b2, and contained 119 residences.<ref name=\"CBS\">Statistics Netherlands (CBS), [http://www.cbs.nl/nl-NL/menu/themas/milieu-natuur-ruimte/ruimte/publicaties/cartografie-geografie/geografische-data/2001-bevolkingskernen-in-nederland.htm ''Bevolkingskernen in Nederland 2001'']. (Statistics are for the continuous built-up area).</ref>\nThe statistical area \"Poederoijen\", which also can include the peripheral parts of the village, as well as the surrounding countryside, has a population of around 860.<ref name=\"CBS2\">Statistics Netherlands (CBS), [http://statline.cbs.nl/ ''Statline: Kerncijfers wijken en buurten 2003-2005'']. As of 1 January 2005.</ref>\n\n==References==\n<references/>\n\n==External links==\n*{{Kuyper|Poederoijen|ge|pouderoijen1}} Map of the former municipality, around 1868.\n\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{Use dmy dates|date=April 2020}}\n\n[[Category:Populated places in Gelderland]]\n[[Category:Former municipalities of Gelderland]]\n[[Category:Zaltbommel]]\n\n\n{{Gelderland-geo-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox settlement\n| name                    = Poederoijen\n| settlement_type         = Village\n| other_name              = <!-- if different from name -->\n| native_name             = <!-- if different from name -->\n| native_name_lang        = nl\n| image_skyline           =\n| image_alt               =\n| image_caption           =\n| image_flag              =\n| image_shield            = Poederoijen wapen.svg\n| nickname                =\n| motto                   =\n| image_map               = LocatieZaltbommel.png\n| map_caption             =\n| image_map1              = Map NL - Zaltbommel - Poederoijen.png\n| map_caption1            = The village centre (red) and the statistical district (light green) of Poederoijen in the municipality of Zaltbommel.\n| pushpin_map             = <!-- Netherlands -->\n| pushpin_label_position  =\n| pushpin_map_caption     = Location in the Netherlands\n| subdivision_type        = [[List of sovereign states|Country]]\n| subdivision_name        = [[Netherlands]]\n| subdivision_type1       = [[Provinces of the Netherlands|Province]]\n| subdivision_name1       = [[Gelderland]]\n| subdivision_type2       = [[List of municipalities of the Netherlands|Municipality]]\n| subdivision_name2       = [[Zaltbommel]]\n| leader_title            =\n| leader_name             =\n| leader_party            =\n| coordinates             = {{coord|51|47|8|N|5|4|49|E|region:NL_type:city(986)|display=inline,title}}\n| coordinates_footnotes   =\n| elevation_m             =\n| elevation_min_m         =\n| elevation_max_m         =\n| area_footnotes          =\n| area_total_km2          =\n| established_title       =\n| established_date        =\n| population_footnotes    = <!-- for references: use <ref> tags -->\n| population_total        = 986\n| population_as_of        = 1 January 2010\n| population_demonym      =\n| population_note         =\n| population_density_km2  = auto\n| timezone                = [[Central European Time|CET]]\n| utc_offset              = +1\n| timezone_DST            = [[Central European Summer Time|CEST]]\n| utc_offset_DST          = +2\n| postal_code_type        = [[List of postal codes in the Netherlands|Postal code]]\n| postal_code             = 5307\n| area_code_type          = [[Telephone numbers in the Netherlands|Dialing code]]\n| area_code               =\n| website                 =\n| footnotes               =\n}}\n'''Poederoijen''' is a village in the [[Netherlands|Dutch]] province of [[Gelderland]]. It is a part of the municipality of [[Zaltbommel]], and lies about 9&nbsp;km southeast of [[Gorinchem]].\n\nPoederoijen was a separate municipality until 1955, when it was merged with [[Brakel, Gelderland|Brakel]].<ref>{{Repertorium Nederlandse Gemeenten}}</ref>\n\nIn 2001, the village of Poederoijen had 398 inhabitants. The built-up area of the village was 0.083&nbsp;km\u00b2, and contained 119 residences.<ref name=\"CBS\">Statistics Netherlands (CBS), [http://www.cbs.nl/nl-NL/menu/themas/milieu-natuur-ruimte/ruimte/publicaties/cartografie-geografie/geografische-data/2001-bevolkingskernen-in-nederland.htm ''Bevolkingskernen in Nederland 2001'']. (Statistics are for the continuous built-up area).</ref>\nThe statistical area \"Poederoijen\", which also can include the peripheral parts of the village, as well as the surrounding countryside, has a population of around 860.<ref name=\"CBS2\">Statistics Netherlands (CBS), [http://statline.cbs.nl/ ''Statline: Kerncijfers wijken en buurten 2003-2005'']. As of 1 January 2005.</ref>\n\n==References==\n<references/>\n\n==External links==\n*{{Kuyper|Poederoijen|ge|pouderoijen1}} Map of the former municipality, around 1868.\n\n{{Use dmy dates|date=September 2010}}\n\n[[Category:Populated places in Gelderland]]\n[[Category:Former municipalities of Gelderland]]\n[[Category:Zaltbommel]]\n\n\n{{Gelderland-geo-stub}}\n", "name_user": "Rich Farmbrough", "label": "safe", "comment": "\u2192\u200eExternal links:Update date format tag and add authority control template", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Poederoijen"}
{"title_page": "September Stakes (United States)", "text_new": "{{Infobox horseraces\n| class         = Discontinued\n| horse race    = September Stakes \n| website       = \n| image         = \n| caption       = \n| location      = [[Sheepshead Bay Race Track]], [[Sheepshead Bay, Brooklyn|Sheepshead Bay]], [[New York (state)|New York]],<br>[[United States]] \n| inaugurated   = 1884\n| race type     = [[Thoroughbred]] - [[Flat racing]]\n| distance      = |align=center|1<span style=\"font-size:80%\">{{Frac|3|16}}</span> miles\n| surface       = Dirt\n| track         = left-handed\n| qualification = Three-year-olds\n| weight        = \n| purse         = \n| bonuses       = \n}}\n\nThe '''September Stakes''' was an American [[Thoroughbred racing|Thoroughbred horse race]] held annually for the twenty-five years between 1884 and 1908 at [[Sheepshead Bay Race Track]] in [[Sheepshead Bay, Brooklyn|Sheepshead Bay]], [[New York (state)|New York]]. A race on dirt, it was open to three-year-old horses of either sex.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://drf.uky.edu/catalog/1900s/drf1907091101/drf1907091101_1_6  |title=Condensed History of the September Stakes |publisher=Daily Racing Form at University of Kentucky Archives |date=1907-09-11 |accessdate=2020-02-11}}</ref> It was contested at various distances as follows:\n*1884-1891 : 1<span style=\"font-size:80%\">{{Frac|3|4}}</span> miles\n*1892-1907 : 1<span style=\"font-size:80%\">{{Frac|3|8}}</span> miles\n*1908 : 1<span style=\"font-size:80%\">{{Frac|1|16}}</span> miles\n\n==Historical notes==\nFirst run on September 4, 1884, the race was won by [[George L. Lorillard|George Lorillard's]] Louisette. Under [[Canada|Canadian]] jockey [[Harry Blaylock]] the filly led all the way and won with ease. <ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.nytimes.com/1884/09/05/archives/four-winning-favorites-six-good-contests-on-the-sheepshead-bay.html |title=Four Winning Favorites - Louisette Never Headed |publisher=[[New York Times]], page 2 |date=1884-09-05|accessdate=2020-02-24}}</ref>\n\nThe [[Thomas Clay McDowell]] colt Batten won the 1899 edition by 20 lengths in a [[Canter and gallop|canter]] with a time of 2:21 4/5 that at the time was only a fraction off the [[Glossary of North American horse racing#Track record/course record|track record]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.nytimes.com/1899/09/08/archives/sheepshead-bay-rages-king-barleycorn-gives-the-talent-a-surprising.html |title=Sheepshead Bay Races |publisher=New York Times, page 5 |date=1899-09-08 |accessdate=2020-04-07}}</ref>\n\n===Future Hall of Fame winners===\nThe September Stakes would produce three winners whose racing careers achieved the sport's ultimate acknowledgement of greatness with induction into the [[National Museum of Racing and Hall of Fame|U.S. Racing Hall of Fame]]. The first was [[Kingston (horse)|Kingston]], a part of the 1955 inaugural class, then [[Beldame]] in 1956 who was followed by [[Salvator (horse)|Salvator]] in 1988.\n\n==The End of a Race and of a Racetrack==\nThe 1908 passage of the [[Hart-Agnew Law|Hart-Agnew]] anti-betting legislation by the [[New York Legislature]] under [[Republican Party (United States)|Republican] [[Governor of New York|Governor]] [[Charles Evans Hughes]] led to a state-wide shutdown of racing in 1911 and 1912.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://drf.uky.edu/catalog/1900s/drf1908011801/drf1908011801_1_7 |title=Penalties in the New York Bills |publisher=Daily Racing Form at University of Kentucky Archives |date=1908-01-18|accessdate=2018-10-26}}</ref> <ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.nytimes.com/1911/07/14/archives/race-track-bill-defeated-in-senate-measure-modifying-directors.html|title=Race Track Bill Defeated In Senate; Measure Modifying Directors' Liability for Gambling Fails of Passage.|first=Special To The New York|last=Times|date=July 14, 1911|publisher=|access-date=September 2, 2017}}</ref> Sheepshead Bay Race Track officials had no choice but to cancel some races in order to maintain others. As such, the final running of the September Stakes took place on September 8, 1908.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.nytimes.com/1908/09/09/archives/whitney-horses-win-three-races-victorious-stable-first-and-second.html |title=Big Chief's September Thomas H. Williams's Colt Beats Fair Play in a Close Contest for Stake Feature at Coney Island Track |publisher=Daily Racing Form at University of Kentucky Archives |date=1908-09-09 |accessdate=2020-03-14}}</ref> <ref>{{cite web|url=https://drf.uky.edu/catalog/1900s/drf1909081701/drf1909081701_1_16 |title=Stake Dates at Sheepshead Bay |publisher=Daily Racing Form at University of Kentucky Archives |date=1909-08-17 |accessdate=2020-04-02}}</ref> A February 21, 1913 ruling by the [[New York Supreme Court, Appellate Division]] saw horse racing return in 1913.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://drf.uky.edu/catalog/1910s/drf1913022201/drf1913022201_1_9 |title= Oral Betting Held Legal: Appellate Division of New York Supreme Court Renders Important Decision |publisher=Daily Racing Form at University of Kentucky Archives |date=1913-02-22 |accessdate=2019-06-29}}</ref> However, it was too late for the Sheepshead Bay horse racing facility and it never reopened.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://drf.uky.edu/catalog/1900s/drf1908121501/drf1908121501_1_7|title=Destruction Wrought by Hughes |publisher=Daily Racing Form at University of Kentucky Archives |date=1908-12-15|accessdate=2018-11-30}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://drf.uky.edu/catalog/1910s/drf1914111701/drf1914111701_1_2 |title=Famous Old Track is Sold |publisher=Daily Racing Form at University of Kentucky Archives |date=1914-11-17|accessdate=2018-11-30}}</ref>\n\n==Records==\n'''Speed record:'''\n* 2:19.00 @ 1<span style=\"font-size:80%\">{{Frac|3|8}}</span> miles: [[Nealon (horse)|Nealon]] (1906)\n* 3:03.00 @ 1<span style=\"font-size:80%\">{{Frac|3|4}}</span> miles: Peg Woffington (1888)\n\n'''Most wins by a [[jockey]]:'''\n* 2 - [[Jim McLaughlin (jockey)|Jim McLaughlin]] (1887, 1889)\n* 2 - [[George M. Odom]] (1900, 1902)\n* 2 - [[Frank O'Neill (jockey)|Frank O'Neill]] (1903, 1904)\n* 2 - [[Willie Simms]] (1894, 1895)\n\n'''Most wins by a [[Horse trainer|trainer]]:'''\n* 2 - [[Matthew Byrnes]] (1884, 1889)\n* 2 - [[William Lakeland (horse trainer)|William Lakeland]] (1888, 1898)\n* 2 - [[John W. Rogers (horse trainer)|John W. Rogers]] (1894, 1900)\n\n'''Most wins by an owner:'''\n* 2 - [[James Ben Ali Haggin]] (1885, 1889)\n* 2 - [[William Lakeland (horse trainer)|William Lakeland]] (1888, 1898)\n\n==Winners==\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\" style=\"font-size:90%\"\n|- \n! style=\"width:30px\" | Year<br>\n! style=\"width:110px\" | Winner<br>\n! style=\"width:20px\" | Age<br>\n! style=\"width:110px\" | Jockey<br>\n! style=\"width:120px\" | Trainer<br>\n! Owner<br>\n! style=\"width:25px\" | Dist.<br> <span style=\"font-size:70%\">([[Mile|Miles]])\n! style=\"width:25px\" | Time<br>\n! style=\"width:25px\" | Win[[United States dollar|$]]<br>\n|-\n|align=center|1908\n|Big Chief\n|align=center|3\n|[[Carroll H. Shilling|Carroll Shilling]]\n|Henry E. Rowell\n|Thomas H. Williams\n|align=center|1<span style=\"font-size:80%\">{{Frac|3|16}}</span>\n|2:10.40\n|$3,100\n|-\n|align=center|1907\n|Blue Book\n|align=center|3\n|R. Lowe\n|Stephen J. Lawler\n|James F. Carroll\n|align=center|1<span style=\"font-size:80%\">{{Frac|3|8}}</span>\n|2:23.00\n|$3,700\n|-\n|align=center|1906\n|[[Nealon (horse)|Nealon]]\n|align=center|3\n|Willie Dugan\n|Herman R. Brandt\n|[[Barney Schreiber]]\n|align=center|1<span style=\"font-size:80%\">{{Frac|3|8}}</span>\n|2:19.00\n|$4,370\n|-\n|align=center|1905\n|Von Tromp\n|align=center|3\n|[[Gene Hildebrand]]\n|[[James G. Rowe Sr.]]\n|[[James R. Keene]]\n|align=center|1<span style=\"font-size:80%\">{{Frac|3|8}}</span>\n|2:21.20\n|$4,065\n|-\n|align=center|1904\n|[[Beldame]]\n|align=center|3\n|[[Frank O'Neill (jockey)|Frank O'Neill]]\n|[[Fred Burlew]]\n|Newton Bennington (Lessee)\n|align=center|1<span style=\"font-size:80%\">{{Frac|3|8}}</span>\n|2:19.60